| Kodak Challenges HP's Printer Sales Model                          |
|   from the jig-is-up dept.                                         |
|   posted by CowboyNeal on Thursday April 26, @20:05 (Printers)     |
|   http://hardware.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/26/2255255     |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

Radon360 writes "Kodak has decided to attempt to [0]buck the trend set by
HP by offering low cost printers and reasonably priced ink cartridges.
Three of their new printers start at $149, with ink cartridges costing
$9.99 for a black cartridge and $14.99 for a five color cartridge. To
counter, HP has announced a release of lower-priced cartridges, though
with less ink and they are still more expensive than Kodak's. It will be
a matter of time to see whether Kodak can upset the practice of ink
cartridge extortion."

