+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

Porsupah writes "The Register reports that "Rep. Jay Inslee (D-WA) and
Rep. Don Manzullo (R-IL) have headed the 'Internet Radio Equality Act,'
which [0]aims to stop the controversial March 2 decision which puts
royalty of a .08 cent per song per listener, retroactively from 2006 to
2010 on internet radio," as imposed by a recent decision from the
Copyright Royalty Board. "If passed, today's bill would set new rates at
7.5 percent of the webcaster's revenue — the same rate paid by satellite
radio.""

