+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

An anonymous reader writes "ZDNet has a short but interesting piece on
the [0]what Google did with its 12GB database when it became a challenge
for the finance department. The database was split into three, says Chris
Schulze, technical program manager for Google — one for the current
financial planning projections, one for the actual current data from
existing HR and general ledger systems, and one storing historic
information. The article says Google has been using a variety of products
from Hyperion (recently bought by Oracle) to manage its internal
financial systems since 2001."

